modules.description: This module creates interactive GTK interfaces for visualizing Mlpost graphics with dynamic controls. It supports adding text inputs that trigger updates, radio menus for selecting actions, and display windows for rendering graphics that refresh automatically when controls change. Use it to build simple GUIs where users adjust parameters and see corresponding graphical output in real time.

This module integrates Mlpost graphics into GTK interfaces, enabling dynamic layout adjustments such as centering, scaling, and fitting figures within GUI components. It provides transformations and event-driven updates, allowing figures to respond to user input and window resizing while maintaining visual consistency. The child module extends this capability by adding interactive controls like text inputs and radio menus, enabling real-time parameter adjustments and immediate graphical feedback. Together, they support building responsive, interactive GTK applications that display and manipulate vector graphics based on user input.
